{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect IEI encoding in UE Radio Capability Information Update Needed field\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE NAS layer contained an incorrect IEI encoding bug in the UeRadioCapabilityInformationUpdateNeeded IES handling. The bug caused TAU Request messages to be malformed when the UE radio capability update flag was included.\n\nThe issue manifested as rejected TAU procedures when UEs attempted to update their radio capabilities. The AMF/NAS layer would reject the messages due to IEI mismatch.\n\nThe root cause was that the encode_u8_ue_radio_capability_information_update_needed function had the IEI hardcoded to 0 instead of the correct 0xA0 value.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeRadioCapabilityInformationUpdateNeeded.c`: Fixed hardcoded IEI value from 0 to 0xA0 and reorganized bit manipulation for clarity\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeRadioCapabilityInformationUpdateNeeded.h`: No changes required\n\n"
}